default“125. Having carefully considered consultat
defaultion responses, we have concluded that there are further limited circumstances where applicants for civil legal aid on certain matters of law (as set out in Schedule 1 to LASPO) would not be required to meet the residence 
defaulttest. The test will not apply to th
defaulte following categories of case (which broadly relate to an individual’s liberty, or where the individual is particularly vulnerable or where the case relates to the protection of children): 
defaultDetention cases 
default(paragraphs 5, 20, 25, 26 and 27 (and challenges 
defaultto the lawfulness of detention by way of judicial review under paragraph 19) of Part 1 of Schedule 1 to LASPO)” 
